            </m:math>
          </equation>
          <para id="id2257640">If <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi mathvariant="bold">a</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi mathvariant="bold">x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> is any vector function of position, <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi mathvariant="bold">a</m:mi><m:mo>•</m:mo><m:mi>τ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> is the projection of <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi mathvariant="bold">a</m:mi></m:math> tangent to the curve. The integral of <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi mathvariant="bold">a</m:mi><m:mo>•</m:mo><m:mi>τ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> around a simple closed curve <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:math> is called the <emphasis effect="italics">circulation</emphasis> of <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>a</m:mi></m:math> around <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:math>.</para>
          <equation id="id2257745"><m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mo>∮</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>C</m:mi>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi mathvariant="bold">a</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>•</m:mo>
                  <m:mi mathvariant="bold">τ</m:mi>
                  <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
                  <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>s</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
