          <para id="id2258603">The vector product has a magnitude equal to the product of the magnitudes and the sine of the angle between the vectors. This gives us the area of a parallelogram corresponding to the area of the differential region.</para>
          <equation id="id2258610">
            <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                <m:mi>S</m:mi>
